%N A397542 Number of pairs (P, I) where P is a partially ordered set on n labeled elements and I is an order ideal (down-set) of P; equivalently, sum over labeled posets P on [n] of the number of antichains of P.
%C A397542 a(n) = Sum_{P} d(P) over the A001035(n) labeled posets P on [n], where d(P) is the number of antichains (equivalently order ideals / down-sets) of P; so a(n) counts the pairs (poset, down-set). This is the k=1 member of the antichain-count moment family k=1..4 used to compute A001035(19).
%H A397542 Rafael Ayala, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2606.31526">The number of labeled partial orders and topologies on 19 points</a>, arXiv:2606.31526 [math.CO], 2026.
%H A397542 Rafael Ayala, <a href="https://github.com/Rafael-Ayala/posets-and-topologies-19">Code and data for the antichain-count moments</a>
%Y A397542 Cf. A001035 (k=0, number of labeled posets), A000798.
%K A397542 nonn,new
